{"id":"bani","term":"Bani","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Built. (1.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 6:46\">1 Chr. 6:46</a>. (2.) One of David’s thirty-seven warriors, a Gadite (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 23:36\">2 Sam. 23:36</a>). (3.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 2:10\">Ezra 2:10</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 10:29\">10:29</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 10:34\">34</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 10:38\">38</a>. (4.) A Levite who was prominent in the reforms on the return from Babylon (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 8:7\">Neh. 8:7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 9:4\">9:4</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 9:5\">5</a>). His son Rehum took part in rebuilding the wall of Jerusalem (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 3:17\">Neh. 3:17</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 6:46","2 Samuel 23:36","Ezra 2:10","Ezra 10:29","Ezra 10:34","Ezra 10:38","Nehemiah 8:7","Nehemiah 9:4","Nehemiah 9:5","Nehemiah 3:17"]}